---
name: legate.issue
description: "Mini-legate's GitHub-issue intake skill. Use when the operator hands you a GitHub issue (a number, `#N`, or full issue URL, optionally followed by extra context) and asks for it to be addressed. The protocol fetches the issue via `gh`, syncs the default branch, launches a worker session that owns the fix end-to-end (investigate → implement → push → open a PR that closes the issue), and records the work in `state.json` as an `issue-<N>` slice with `kind: \"issue\"`, so the deterministic loop (including its gated auto-merge) and `legate.babysit` track its PR through merge identically to a Smithy slice. Triggers: an operator message naming a GitHub issue (`issue 42`, `issue #42`, `issue https://github.com/Owner/Repo/issues/42`, `please fix issue 42 — focus on the migration path`). Skip on heartbeat ticks (those are handled by the deterministic loop plus heartbeat skills) and skip when no issue reference is present in the operator message."
